				\begin{document}$$\mathop \lambda \nolimits_{QSSR}$$\end{document} is substituted by 10 μm. The cross resonator is considered an electric ring resonator (ERR)26 that is able to strongly manipulate the incident IR radiations. The major and minor axes of the designed CEs control the electric response while the magnetic response is tuned by the thickness of the dielectric layer27. The resonant frequency of a regular cross resonator, i.e. crossed rectangles, can be estimated from the microwave regime using the formula28:2λCE=lπεTiO2(w/tm)ln(tm/w)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
